îóŸRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2024-04-13-twin0242.mdŸ@cbdddb47d7405863727f70aa5c8c1d2fbe9a82a993982e4ef50718c43df3567eπThis week in Nushell #242ëßNushell⁄sayax79 made lots of dataframe improvements: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12220] moved dataframes support to a plugin
 (this is huge!), 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12501] ensured that two columns named 'index' don't exist when converting a DataFrame to a nu value
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12487] added a short flag -c to 
``polars append``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12486] handled relative paths correctly on polars 
``to-(parquet|nuon|arrow|etc)``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12472] displayed span information, creation time, and size with 
``polars ls``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12462] showed full help when running the 
``polars``
 command
devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12493] switched the CI to use macOS-13 instead of macOS-latest, due to failures
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12439] added a 
``GetSpanContents``
 engine call
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12437] isolated tests from user config
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12410] added a 
``--no-newline``
 option to 
``nu``
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12497] bumped Nushell to latest reedline
, introduced 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12494] better logging for the 
``shell_integration``
 setting
, and aimed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12449] to be a bit more precise with REPL logging
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12495] fixed up plugin CI for macOS
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12476] bumped version to 
``0.92.3``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12471] bumped our Rust version to stable
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12455] updated MSRV following 
``rust-toolchain.toml``
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12480] updated 
``kill``
 to return a single value instead of a stream
, did a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12479] ``drop``
 refactor
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12478] refactored 
``first``
 and 
``last``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12436] mentioned 
``print``
 in the 
``echo``
 help text
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12433] renamed 
``IoStream``
 to 
``OutDest``
amtoine 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12470] fixed 
``std log``
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12465] forced 
``timeit``
 to not capture stdout
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12327] made 
``ls``
 and 
``du``
 support rest parameters
singh-priyank 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12443] fixed a bug with negative file sizes for 
``into filesize``
oornaque 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12442] fixed typo in help stor import
texastoland 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12339] lexed whitespace in input-output types
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12338] ensured 
``currently_parsed_cwd``
 is set for config files
